deck: Cecil Bronstein, a gun wielding, cigarette smoking, badass leaves Wisconsin. The King of the Dead is tired of eating skinny prisoners in London and leaves for America.
name: As the World Churns

deck: The Zombie King's ship is sinking in the Atlantic. Cecil meets a grandma in a suit of armor and her hulk of a grandson Eddie.
name: Coming to America

description: Then one day, Seiji wakes up to discover his "devil's right hand" has turned into...a miniature gal named Midori! Strangely enough, Midori is a real girl who is just as surprised as Seiji to find out she has now become--literally--Seiji's right hand! It turns out Midori has always had a crush on Seiji, and her desperate wish to be connected to him has somehow come true...maybe all too true!

Batgirl and Robin have to channel Batman's detective skills in order to catch Clayface and Man-Bat, who are still on the loose-but how do you follow in the footsteps of The Dark Crusader, who's always two steps ahead of everyone-"What Would Batman Do?" part 2 of 2.
name: What Would Batman Do? Part 2 of 2

description: What would YOU do with $11? The mysterious liaison of Gosford Wobbledon is paying a visit to Riverdale, with a gift of eleven dollars for Archie and his friends. What does it all mean? And more importantly, could a simple $11 change the gang's lives FOREVER?! Find out in this digital-only collection of this bizarre adventure!

volume.name: Archie & Friends: Legend of the Elevenaire
